data.text: @CaudalRaphe @TimHoran12 Lets compare my insight on school boy scrums to another that I have some experience with - child birth. I have seen my beautiful wife go through 4 labour’s and feel in some ways I might have been on the “field” but the reality is I could not explain the experience first hand.

@mjgoodenco @TimHoran12 Clearly turning up for however many years hasn’t given you any insight

#don’ttalktomeaboutboats
@CaudalRaphe @TimHoran12 Only 25 years playing in the front row.

@mjgoodenco @TimHoran12 Not as funny as assuming someone with his extensive experience in the game and who’s also an ambassador for Spinal Injuries Australia knows nothing about prevention strategies for Rugby forwards.

What’s your expertise to criticise him?

@CaudalRaphe @TimHoran12 I agree, training is critical to educate kids about risks and learn correct positions, it’s just funny having these comments coming from guy who spent his playing career in the backs.
@mjgoodenco @TimHoran12 Tim’s idea for formal scrum training is one of the best ideas I’ve head in ages.  Not just to avoid neck injuries but to raise the players skills.  Has huge merit.
